<bug>
    <id>23180</id>
    <title>APT repository contains bad 'component' in Release file(s)</title>
    <description>
        <paragraph id="1">
            <sentence id="1.1">In the apt repository hosted at apt.dockerproject.org , the 'Release' file for component 'main' contains this:</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="2">
            <sentence id="2.1">"'
Architectures: amd64 i386
Codename: ubuntu-precise
Components: testing
Date: Wed, 01 Jun 2016 22:19:01 UTC
Label: Docker APT Repository
Origin: Docker
Suite: ubuntu-precise
...
"'</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="3">
            <sentence id="3.1">(file is at: https://apt.dockerproject.org/repo/dists/ubuntu-precise/main/binary-amd64/Release)</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="4">
            <sentence id="4.1">Notice that the components section only contains 'testing'.</sentence>
            <sentence id="4.2">However this is the 'Releases' file for component 'main'.</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="5">
            <sentence id="5.1">The same problem exists for 'experimental' as well.</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="6">
            <sentence id="6.1">Some tools seem to trip on this (notably: aptly - which is a handly tool to painlessly mirror repositories).</sentence>
            <sentence id="6.2">Without this, I cannot mirror the 'main' component of the repository.</sentence>
            <sentence id="6.3">:(</sentence>
        </paragraph>
    </description>
</bug>
